14/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The opposition alliance between the National Liberal Party and the Democratic Party is adding one more partner -- the Humanist Party (PUR) -- for the second round of the local elections on 20 June.
The party leaders decided Sunday (13 June) to work with PUR to beat the ruling Social Democrat Party in the run-off.
In other news, Interior Minister Ioan Rus tendered his resignation on Saturday.
He is in the run-off for mayor of Cluj Napoca.
Rus says his decision is final, regardless of the election outcome.
(Rompres - 14/06/04;
Mediafax, Nine o'clock - 13/06/04)
